{"lemma":"مُعَيَّنَةٍ","slug":"مُعَيَّنَةٍ","root":"ع.#.ن","root_slug":"ع-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-ن","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُعَيَّن","root":"عين","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31301","n31302","n31303"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"well, spring, water source","tags":["archaic"],"examples":[{"text":"يَطُوفُ عَلَيْهِمْ وِلْدَانٌ مُّخَلَّدُونَ بِأَكْوَابٍ وَأَبَارِيقَ وَكَأْسٍ مِّن مَّعِينٍ","english":"There will circulate among them young boys made eternal, with beakers, pitchers and a glass of spring water."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of عَيَّنَ (ʕayyana).","tags":["active","archaic","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of عَيَّنَ (ʕayyana)","tags":["archaic","form-of","participle","passive"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"definite, clear, determined, known","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"rhombic","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rhombus","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the state of Maʿīn in ancient Yemen","tags":["archaic"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew מַעְיָן (ma'ayán, “spring, fountain”).\n\nDerived from the active participle and passive participle of عَيَّنَ (ʕayyana).\n\nFrom Old South Arabian 𐩣𐩲𐩬 (mʿn)."},"ipa":["/ma.ʕiːn/","/mu.ʕaj.jin/","/mu.ʕaj.jan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31301","headword_ar":"مَعِينٌ","root":"Eyn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Smitten with the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoyuwnN","text_ar":"مَعْيُونٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the complete form: (S, TA:) or, accord. to Ez-Zejjájee, the former has this meaning, but ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaEoyuwnu","text_ar":"المَعْيُونُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aal~a*iY fiyhi EayonN","text_ar":"اَلَّذِى فِيهِ عَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in which the last word is probably a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayobN","text_ar":"عَيْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in whom is a fault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defect"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (L, TA.) A poet says, (S,) namely, 'Abbás, (TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qado kaAna qawomuka yaHosabuwnaka say~idFA\n                      \n                     ↓ \n      waA_ixalu A^in~aka say~idN maEoyuwnu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, used to reckon thee a chief; but I think that them art a chief smitten with the evil eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, perhaps,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in whom is a fault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defect"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='N maEiynN","text_ar":"مَا=ءٌ مَعِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoyuwnN","text_ar":"مَعْيُونٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water of which one has reached the springs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sources, by digging:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water that is apparent"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAhirN","text_ar":"ظَاهِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for which the CK has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZAhrN","text_ar":"ظاهرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seen by the eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running upon the surface of the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) Bedr Ibn-'Ámir El-Hudhalee says."},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      maA='N yujim~u liHaAfirK maEoyuwni"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water collecting for a digger of which the springs have been reached by digging"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; the last word, it as said, being put by him in the gen. case because of the proximity [to a word in that case, agreeably with a poetic license of which there are many exs.],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoyuwnN","text_ar":"مَعْيُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as it is an epithet relating to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m='","text_ar":"م=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": Respecting the measure of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiynN","text_ar":"مَعِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which IB derives from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayonu AlmaA='i","text_ar":"عَيْنُ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". and explain as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the source apparent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"there are differences of opinion; some say that it is an instance of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"though not having a verb; and some, that of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmEonu","text_ar":"المعْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying the drawing of water. (TA.) In the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino","text_ar":"اـِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnati Alba$aru maEiynFA laA tunozaHu","text_ar":"كَانَتِ البَشَرُ مَعِينًا لَا تُنْزَحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If the well be one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a running spring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that willnot be entirely exhausted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mEynA","text_ar":"معينا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made masc. to accord with the word ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b}r","text_ar":"بئر"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is masc. in form though fem. by usage]; or it is thus because it is imagined to be of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiyl","text_ar":"فَعِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwl","text_ar":"مَفْعُول"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or because it is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAta maEiynK","text_ar":"ذَاتَ مَعِينٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water running upon the surface of the earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) In the Kur xxxvii. 44. [and in like manner in lvi. 18.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiyn","text_ar":"مَعِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wine running upon the surface of the earth, like rivers of water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoyuwnapN","text_ar":"مَعْيُونَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A spring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"source, having a continued increase of water"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Sa'eed, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n31302","headword_ar":"مُعَيَّنٌ","root":"Eyn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  A garment"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figured with eyes"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brj","text_ar":"برج"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or a garment"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the figuring of which are small"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraAbiyE","text_ar":"تَرَابِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quadrangular forms"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarobiyE","text_ar":"تَرْبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the eyes of wild animals."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  And (assumed tropical:)  A bull"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a blackness between his eyes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bull;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because of the largeness of his eyes: or so called because"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having spots of black and white, as though there were eyes upon his skin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 293.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2219},{"kind":"text","text":"And (assumed tropical:)  Locusts ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraAd","text_ar":"جَرَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which, when stripped of the integument, are seen to be white and red:"},{"kind":"text","text":"mentioned by Az in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ynE","text_ar":"ينع"},{"kind":"text","text":", on the authority of ISh. (TA.)       -A2-  [Also, as pass. part. n. of 2, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Individuated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particularized;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distinguished from the generality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aggregate:"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see the verb. Hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niy~apN muEay~anapN","text_ar":"نِيَّةٌ مُعَيَّنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A distinct, particular,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"special, purpose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a purpose made distinct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is allowable for one to attribute the action to the purpose, tropically; and thus to say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niy~apN muEay~inapN","text_ar":"نِيَّةٌ مُعَيِّنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A distinguishing purpose"},{"kind":"text","text":"], using the act. part. n. (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n31303","headword_ar":"مُعَيِّنٌ","root":"Eyn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see an ex. of its fem. in what next precedes."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}